<emphasis box="[224,388,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Axina nigrifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schenkling S." box="[396,621,1379,1404]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="241 - 320" refId="ref45467" refString="Schenkling S. 1906. Die Cleriden des Deutschen Entomologischen National-Museums, nebst beschreibungen neuer Arten. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 1: 241 - 320." type="journal article" year="1906">Schenkling, 1906: 253</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[631,734,1380,1404]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<typeStatus box="[631,734,1380,1404]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Lectotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Female. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[832,1010,1379,1404]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Here designated.</emphasis>
Type locality: Puerto Cabello (Venezuela) (SDEI). 
<typeStatus box="[340,480,1411,1435]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
. One specimen. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[648,983,1411,1435]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<collectingCountry box="[648,758,1411,1435]" name="Venezuela" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[768,983,1411,1435]" country="Venezuela" name="Carabobo" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Estado de Carabobo</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
, Puerto Cabello (SDEI). 
<treatmentCitation author="Corporaal JB" box="[1238,1437,1411,1435]" page="98" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" year="1950">
<bibRefCitation author="Corporaal JB" box="[1238,1437,1411,1435]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" refId="ref44328" refString="Corporaal JB. 1950. Cleridae. In: Hinks WD (ed.). Coleopterorum catalogus supplementa, Pars 23 (editio secunda). W. Junk; Gravenhage, The Netherlands. 373 p." type="book" year="1950">Corporaal 1950: 98</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
. There is indication that Schenkling examined more than one specimen in his description of this species, but he did not select a 
<typeStatus box="[378,469,1474,1498]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
, therefore, I invoke Recommendation 73F of the 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Code of Zoological Nomenclature" box="[968,1100,1474,1498]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" refId="ref44854" refString="(ICZN) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 1999. 4 th Edition. Adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature; London, United Kingdom. 306 p." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and designate a 
<typeStatus box="[1270,1362,1474,1498]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this nominal species.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="33.[192,1440,1546,1607]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1546,1572]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The elytral apex is obtuse in specimens of this species, which is not the case in superficially similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2020" box="[343,500,1581,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutipennis">
<emphasis box="[343,362,1581,1607]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[375,500,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">acutipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the elytral apex is subacuminate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[191,1444,1623,1927]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,363,1623,1649]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[368,411,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Size</emphasis>
. Length 6.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[674,762,1623,1650]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[769,828,1624,1649]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[904,994,1623,1649]" captionStart="Figures 110–113" captionStartId="68.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-11@68.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Figures 110–113. Habitus of Axina species. 110) Axina vista. 111) A. nigrifrons. 112) A. ochra. 113) A. analis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565035/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Fig. 111</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1003,1064,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium bicolorous, frons black, remainder flavotestaceous; antenna testaceous; thorax and abdomen flavotestaceous; elytra bicolorous, basal 1⁄5 and apical 1⁄5 black, remainder flavotestaceous; legs bicolorous, prothoracic femora flavotestaceous, basal ½ of mesothoracic and metathoracic femora flavotestaceous, remainder of femora and tibiae black, tarsi brown. 
<emphasis box="[1374,1433,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons slightly wider than length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 40/10. 
<emphasis box="[1234,1312,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 98/130; elytra, asetiferous punctures arranged into striae, striated punctures extend to elytral middle, width of interstitial spaces variable, elytral apex obtuse; EL/EW 360/65. 
<emphasis box="[375,479,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus, phallobasic lobes very short and abruptly narrowed in distal ½, narrowly separated; phallic plates serrate, phallic apex extended; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[191,1440,213,308]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,310,213,239]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Variation.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[315,358,214,240]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Size</emphasis>
. Length 6.0–9.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[668,804,214,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="1.9" valueMax="2.2" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.2 mm</quantity>
. There may be one or 2 dark spots between the black basal and apical elytral region, and the black portion on the apical 1⁄5 of the elytra may be faintly visible or reduced to a narrow fascia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[192,1441,323,384]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,377,323,349]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Natural history.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[707,785,323,349]" name="Bolivia" pageId="34" pageNumber="33">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
during October through December, some at altitudes that range from 
<quantity box="[323,451,357,384]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="400.0" valueMax="430.0" valueMin="370.0">
370– 
<specimenCount box="[377,451,357,384]" pageId="34" pageNumber="33" type="generic">430 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
